.TH GAT-UI 1 "2026-06-04" "gat 0.3.0" "gat Manual"
.SH NAME
gat-ui \- interactive TUI dashboard
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B gat ui
.RB [ \-\-fast ]
.br
.B gat dashboard
.RB [ \-\-fast ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
Opens a keyboard-driven dashboard, designed to run inside a tmux pane, with two
tabs (Worktrees and Sessions) showing change stats, idle time, and
descriptions. From the dashboard you can navigate, filter, switch to a session,
edit a description, and remove a worktree.
.PP
The TUI is gated behind the optional
.I tui
Cargo feature so the standard build stays lean. Build or install it with
.RB ` "cargo install \-\-path . \-\-features tui" `.
Without the feature,
.B gat ui
prints a message explaining how to enable it.
.SH "KEY BINDINGS"
.TP
.BR j " / " k ", arrows"
Move the selection.
.TP
.B Tab
Toggle the Worktrees and Sessions list.
.TP
.B Enter
Switch to (or open) the selected worktree's session.
.TP
.B d
Describe the selected worktree.
.TP
.B x
Remove the selected worktree (asks
.IR y/N ).
.TP
.B /
Incremental filter
.RB ( Enter
commits,
.B Esc
cancels).
.TP
.B r
Refresh the snapshot.
.TP
.BR q " / " Esc
Quit.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-\-fast
Skip dirty/merged/change-stat checks for instant startup.
.SH EXAMPLES
.RS
.EX
gat ui
gat ui \-\-fast
.EE
.RE
.SH "SEE ALSO"
.BR gat (1),
.BR gat\-list (1),
.BR gat\-sessions (1)
